cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on facial image hallucination using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also involves the use of temporal consistency modelling and recurrent exploitation of reconstructed results, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM), deep learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also involves the modelling of coherence of structural facial features, which could potentially fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
